==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sparger
<hw>Spar"ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>asperger</ets> to sprinkle, L. <ets>aspergere</ets>,
<ets>spargere</ets>.]</ety> <def>A vessel with a perforated cover, for
sprinkling with a liquid; a sprinkler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- 2. A tube with a perforated or fritted end, to pass gases as
small bubbles through a liquid. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sparhawk</ent>⟦br⟧
